|Champions League second qualifying round]]\n|result1=CL2\n|col_EL2=blue1|text_EL2=Qualification to [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|Europa League second qualifying round]] \n|note_res_EL2=The winners of the [[2011\u201312 Lithuanian Football Cup]] competition, \u017dalgiris Vilnius, qualified for the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|second qualifying round]] of UEFA Europa League. As they finished second, the fourth-placed team of the league also qualified for the Europa League.\n|result2=EL2\n|col_EL1=blue2|text_EL1=Qualification to [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|Europa League first qualifying round]] \n|note_res_EL1=EL2\n|result3=EL1|result4=EL1\n|col_RLL=red1|text_RLL=Relegation to Lower leagues \n|note_res_RLL=FK Ma\u017eeikiai, FBK Kaunas and FC Klaip\u0117da were not granted a [[2012 A Lyga]] licence; Kaunas will compete in the second-level I Lyga, while Ma\u017eeikiai and Klaip\u0117da will not play in any of the two highest leagues in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 met\u0173 Lietuvos futbolo A lygoje rungtyniaus 10 komand\u0173 |url=http://www.lff.lt/lt/article/2012_metu_lietuvos_futbolo_a_lygoje_rungtyniaus_10_komandu|publisher=[[Lithuanian Football Federation]]|accessdate=1 March 2012|language=Lithuanian|date=2 February 2012}}</ref>\n|result9=RLL|result12=RLL\n|col_R1=red1|text_R1=Relegation to [[I Lyga]] \n|note_res_R1=RLL\n|result10=R1\n|class_rules=1st points; 2nd head-to-head points; 3rd head-to-head goal difference; 4th goal difference; 5th number of goals scored; 6th number of wins.<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 MET\u0172 LIETUVOS FUTBOLO FEDERACIJOS VAR\u017dYB\u0172 NUOSTATAI|url=http://www.lff.lt/article/17246/2011_m_lff_varzybu_nuostatai.pdf|publisher=[[Lithuanian Football Federation]]|accessdate=13 March 2011}}{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> \n|update=complete\n|source=[https://int.soccerway.com/national/lithuania/a-lyga/2011