eague season\n| competition      = [[A Lyga]]\n| season           = 2011\n| winners          = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]<br>6th title\n| relegated        = \n| continentalcup1  = [[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]\n| continentalcup2  = [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FK \u017dalgiris Vilnius|\u017dalgiris]]<br>[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]<br>[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]]\n| continentalcup3  = [[2012\u201313 Baltic League|Baltic League]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]<br>[[FK \u017dalgiris Vilnius|\u017dalgiris]]<br>[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]<br>[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]]<br>[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]\n| league topscorer = \n| biggest home win = {{nobreak|[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]] 13\u20130 [[FK Atlantas|Atlantas]]}}\n| biggest away win = [[FK Dainava Alytus|Dainava]] 0\u20136 [[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]\n| highest scoring  = [[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]] 13\u20130 [[FK Atlantas|Atlantas]]\n| matches          = 198\n| total goals      = 560\n| longest wins     = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]], [[VMFD \u017dalgiris Vilnius|\u017dalgiris]]<br>(8 games each)<ref name=\"ALStats\">{{cite web |title=A Lyga - 2011 |url=http://www.whoscored.com/Regions/127/Tournaments/159/Lithuania-A-Lyga |work=WhoScored.com |publisher=WhoScored.com |accessdate=14 December 2011 }}</ref>\n| longest unbeaten = [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]<br>(19 games)<ref name=\"ALStats\" />\n| longest winless  = [[FC Klaip\u0117da]]<br>(20 games)<ref name=\"ALStats\" />\n| longest losses   = [[FC Klaip\u0117da]]<br>(17 games)<ref name=\"ALStats\" />\n| prevseason       = [[2010 A Lyga|2010]]\n| nextseason       = [[2012 A Lyga|2012]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2011 A Lyga''' was the 22nd season of the [[A Lyga]], the top-tier [[Association football|football]] league of [[Lithuania]]. The season began on 12 March 2011 and ended on 6 November 2011.<ref name=schedule>{{cite web|title=PDF dokumentas 2011 m. LFF A lygos, taur\u0117s ir tarptautini\u0173 rungtyni\u0173 tvarkara\u0161tis|url=http://www.lff.lt/article/17243/2011_lff_a_lygos_taures_ir_tarptautiniu_tvarkarastis_12.pdf|publisher=[[Lithuanian Football Federation]]|accessdate=9 March 2011|language=Lithuanian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202233606/http://www.lff.lt/article/17243/2011_lff_a_lygos_taures_ir_tarptautiniu_tvarkarastis_12.pdf|archive-date=2013-12-02|url-status=dead}}</ref>  [[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]] were the defending champions, having won their third consecutive title at the end of the [[2010 A Lyga|2010 season]].\n\n==Teams==\nThe league will see a change in the number of teams once again as twelve teams were granted a licence for 2011,<ref name=numberofteams>{{cite web|title=2011 met\u0173 LFF A lygoje \u017eais 12 komand\u0173, paskelbtas tvarkara\u0161tis|url=http://www.lff.lt/lt/article/2011_metu_lff_a_lygoje_zais_12_komandu|publisher=[[Lithuanian Football Federation]]|accessdate=9 March 2011|language=Lithuanian}}</ref> one more than in the [[2010 A Lyga|2010 season]].\n\n[[FK V\u0117tra]] were expelled over financial troubles after 16 matches of the 2010 season;<ref>{{cite web|title=\"V\u0117trai\" gresia pa\u0161alinimas \u012f \u017eemesn\u0119 lyg\u0105|url=http://www.lff.lt/lt/article/vetrai_gresia_pasalinimas_i_zemesne_lyga|publisher=[[Lithuanian Football Federation]]|accessdate=9 March 2011|language=Lithuanian}}</ref> their records were annulled and the team was subsequently disbanded.{{citation needed|date=March 2011}} From the remaining ten clubs, [[FK Atletas Kaunas|Atletas Kaunas]], who finished in last place at the end of the season, were the only team not to apply for a 2011 top-level licence. Atletas therefore played at the second level in 2011.\n\nThree new teams were admitted to the league, unbeaten<ref>{{cite web|title=Lithuania - 1 Lyga 2010|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/lithuania/1-lyga/2010/regular-season/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=10 March 2011}}</ref> 2010 [[I Lyga]] champions [[FBK Kaunas]], seventh-placed team [[FK Atlantas|Atlantas Klaip\u0117da]] and [[FK Dainava Alytus|Dainava Alytus]], a merger between I Lyga runners-up Alytis Alytus and third-placed city rivals Vidzgiris.<ref name=\"history\">{{cite web|title=FK Dainava Alytus|url=http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/Vereinsprofilnew.php?ID=2503|publisher=Weltfussballarchiv|accessdate=11 March 2011}}</ref> FBK Kaunas and Atlantas made their return after two seasons in the lower divisions of the Lithuanian league system, while Dainava had their debut in the A Lyga, as neither of its predecessor clubs played at the Lithuanian top level in its history.\n\n{{Location map+|Lithuania|float=right|width=400|caption=Location of teams in the '''2010 A Lyga'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.71|long=21.13|label=[[FK Atlantas|Atlantas]]<br />[[FC Klaip\u0117da|Klaip\u0117da]]|position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.702778|long=21.403333|label=[[FK Banga Garg\u017edai|Banga]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.4 |long=24.05|label=[[FK Dainava Alytus|Dainava]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.733333|long=24.35|label=[[FK Ekranas|Ekranas]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.9|long=23.933333|label=[[FBK Kaunas|Kaunas]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.97|long=23.85|label=[[FK Kruoja Pakruojis|Kruoja]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=56.3|long=22.33|label=[[FK Ma\u017eeikiai|Ma\u017eeikiai]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.933333|long=23.316667|label=[[FK \u0160iauliai|\u0160iauliai]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.566667|long=23.35|label=[[FK S\u016bduva Marijampol\u0117|S\u016bduva]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=55.25|long=22.283333|label=[[FK Tauras Taurag\u0117|Tauras]]}}\n{{Location map~|Lithuania|lat=54.683333|long=25.283333|label=[[FK \u017dalgiris Vilnius|\u017dalgiris]]}}\n}