web|url=https://rajassembly.nic.in/MemberBioData.aspx|title=Rajasthan Legislative Assembly Member Information|website=rajassembly.nic.in}}</ref> As member of the [[Indian National Congress|Congress party]] <ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rajpcc.com/mukeshbhakar|title=Indian National Congress Party|website=www.rajpcc.com}}</ref> and as the President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]].\n\n== Political life ==\nHe elected State President of NSUI Rajasthan.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-JAI-mukesh-bhakar-became-the-state-chief-of-nsui-4164425-NOR.html|title=NSUI \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936\u093e\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u092c\u0928\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u093e\u0915\u0930|date=31 January 2013|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref>  During his tenure NSUI made come back in Rajasthan University after 12 years in Largest University of Rajasthan.<ref>https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/jaipur/news/RAJ-JAI-10-candidates-for-presidents-post-rajasthan-4719233-NOR.html.</ref> After completion of his term National president nominated him National Secretary. Congress Party gave him an opportunity to contest general elections of Rajasthan State assembly in December 2018 where he successfully managed a win by margin of 12947 votes against 3 times MLA Thakur Manohar Singh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/election-result-2018/rajasthan-election-result-2018/nagaur/ladnun/mukesh-bhakar/|title=Ladnun Congress Candidate Mukesh Bhakar, Mukesh Bhakar vs Manohar Singh, \u0932\u093e\u0921\u0928\u0942\u0902 \u0938\u0940\u091f \u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0902\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u092e\u0940\u0926\u0935\u093e\u0930 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u0915\u0930|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/elections/rajasthan-election/article/ladnun-assembly-constituency-election-2018-rajasthan-assembly-polls-rajasthan-vasundh